@{
    ViewBag.Title = "FAQ";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_LayoutLanding.cshtml";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1>FAQ</h1>

    <p>
        <h3>1. What is iiSnap?</h3>
        iiSnap is a new social e-commerce platform that brings people together to create a buying power that translates to great savings.
    </p>

    <p>
        <h3>2. Why is it important I invite my friends to join iiSnap?</h3>
        The most important thing to understand is the power of consumers. For a great shopping experience you’re with friends and the ‘bargaining power’ value is in

        your hands. The bigger your social network, the more potential savings you can

        gain.
    </p>

    <p>
        <h3>3. Can I invite my friends to join iiSnap now?</h3>
        Absolutely! Once you have joined the invitation list, you will receive an e-mail confirmation. In this email you will find a special link and instructions on how to invite your friends to iiSnap.
        For every friend who will join the invitation list via this link, you will be entitiled to receive additional bonus Snap Points upon their later registration on iiSnap.
    </p>

    <p>
        <h3>4. What does it mean "I can shop with my friends online"?</h3>
        You can ask your friends what they think, see what products they like, shop together for the same product and earn rewards while you all having fun!
        If you know one or few of your friends who would like something, why not share the fun and get rewarded for it?
    </p>

    <p>
        <h3>5. Why would the price drop when I join a sale?</h3>
        Our algorythm drops the price based on the current demand for a product! More people join the sale, lower the price drops.
    </p>

    <p>
        <h3>6. Why it is important to invite my friends to join iiSnap?</h3>
        The most important thing to understand, is that the power for great shopping experience and value is in your hands! Bigger your friends network is, the more potential savings you and your friends can achieve.
    </p>

    <p>
        <h3>7. When will iiSnap go live?</h3>
        iiSnap will launch in summer 2015
    </p>

</div>